==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionCascadeHorizDimension''' tool evenly spaces horizontal dimensions.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCascadeHorizDimensionExample.png|400px]]
{{Caption|On the right the evenly spaced horizontal dimensions}}

==Usage==

# Optionally specify the cascade spacing with the [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionSelectLineAttributes.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionSelectLineAttributes|TechDraw ExtensionSelectLineAttributes]] tool.
# Select two or more horizontal dimensions.
# The first dimension defines the position. This dimension will not be moved, the other dimensions will be positioned relative to this dimension.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCascadeHorizDimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionCascadeHorizDimension|Cascade Horizontal Dimensions]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Attributes/Modifications → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCascadeHorizDimension.svg|16px]] Cascade Horizontal Dimensions}} option from the menu.
# The dimensions are evenly spaced and their dimension texts are centered.

==Notes==

* The tool can also be used to center the dimension text of a single dimension.


